(1) To keep the Allied States regularly informed on the work
                                    of the Council of Foreign Ministers in connection with the
                                    preparation of the Peace Treaty;

(3) To communicate to the Allied States with the agreement of
                                    the originating Government the memoranda, statements and other
                                    documents submitted to the Council of Foreign Ministers;

(a) on the questions set forth in the memoranda and oral
                                    statements of the representatives of the Allied States relating
                                    to the German problem;
